binaryTree

Class BinaryTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • binaryTree.BinaryTree<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of value stored in the tree.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BTree<T>

    public class BinaryTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BTree<T>
    A partial implementation of sorted binary trees.

    The three constructors (construct an empty tree (BinaryTree(), or a tree with a root value but no subtrees (BinaryTree(Comparable), or a tree with a root value and left and right subtrees (BinaryTree(Comparable, BinaryTree, BinaryTree)), as well as the isEmpty() method are already implemented.

    For the remaining methods specified in the BTree interface (insert(Comparable), getValue(), setValue(Comparable), getLeft(), setLeft(BTree), getRight(), setRight(BTree), contains(Comparable), and traverse()) only a "stub" is provided. For the logbook exercise you should implement these methods.

    Don't forget to test your implementation!

    Version:
    December 2019.
    Author:
    Hugh Osborne.
